array:34 [ "_token" => "SCqQ7pqjOfVH0PO41UQROHcgSnx2xf2BOyz7EMXH" "return_url" => "http://booktours.io/admin/tours" "ref_mainpath" => "http://booktours.io/admin/tours" "ref_parameter" => "return_url=http://booktours.io/admin/tours&parent_id=&parent_field=" "tour_code" => "TTNFDT001" "category_id" => "1" "title" => "Toronto To Niagara Falls Day Tour" "slug" => "toronto-to-niagara-falls-day-tour" "location" => "Niagara Falls Grand Island Regional Municipality of Niagara" "input-latitude-location" => "43.0895577" "input-longitude-location" => "-79.08494359999997" "attractions" => "Niagara Fall" "country" => "96" "province" => "Uttar Pradesh" "hour" => "00" "minute" => "00" "second" => "00" "departure_time" => "08:15:15" "departure_point" => "Downtown, Toronto, ON, Canada" "input-latitude-departure_point" => "0" "input-longitude-departure_point" => "0" "return_point" => "CA Mississauga Regional Municipality of Peel" "input-latitude-return_point" => "43.682263" "input-longitude-return_point" => "-79.60979299999997" "type" => "on" "return_time" => "00:00:00" "tour_duration" => "9.5 Hours" "discount" => "0" "overview" => """

Niagara Falls is home to one of the most stunning Natural wonders, however, there is so much more to see and experience in Niagara. Our Toronto to Niagara Falls Day Tour will take you from the Falls to the stunning views of the Falls view Buffet where you can be treated to a sumptuous meal overlooking the Niagara Falls (lunch buffet is an optional add-on). We then travel back in time to the picturesque town of Niagara-on-the-Lake. This quaint town still retains its 19th century charm from the Victorian era as well as it's stunning architecture.

\r\n

No Toronto to Niagara Falls Tour is complete without visiting one of the regions many wineries, where you will learn how grapes are grown, crushed and pressed to produce some of the world's finest wines and participate in a wine tasting.

""" "itinerary" => """
    \r\n
  • \r\n 1.\r\n

    Day Tour Begins

    \r\n
    \r\n

    Free pick up from all hotels and B&Bs in Toronto, Mississauga, Brampton, Etobicoke & Oakville, including Hotels near the Toronto Pearson International Airport. If you are not staying at a hotel or B&B, you would be asked to come to one of our centralized pickup locations. 1.5 Hours (90 minutes) drive from Toronto to Niagara Falls.

    \r\n
    \r\n
    \r\n Downtown, Toronto, ON, Canada \r\n 8:15 - 9:15 am \r\n
    \r\n
    • \r\n
  • \r\n 2.\r\n

    Arrive at Canadian side of Niagara Falls.

    \r\n
    \r\n

    You will be able to see the beautiful Niagara Falls even before the bus stops!

    \r\n
    \r\n
    \r\n Niagara Falls, ON, Canada \r\n 11:00 - 11:30 am \r\n
    \r\n
    • \r\n
  • \r\n 3.\r\n

    Hornblower Niagara Cruise (Seasonal)

    \r\n
    \r\n

    FREE Admission to Hornblower Niagara Boat Cruise (All tickets include Fast Track access via the Funicular Incline Railway). This attraction is seasonal. If the Hornblower cruise is not available (usually in the winter months) then you will experience the Journey Behind the Falls attraction, where you will explore the tunnels behind the Niagara Falls.

    \r\n
    \r\n
    \r\n Hornblower Niagara Cruises, Niagara Falls, ON, Canada \r\n 11:35 am \r\n
    \r\n
    • \r\n
  • \r\n 4.\r\n

    Lunch and Free Time to Explore Niagara Falls

    \r\n
    \r\n

    Free time to eat lunch, souvenir shop and explore! ToNiagara offers a delicious Buffet Lunch Add-On at the Sheraton Fallsview restaurant, it is a healthy alternative to the fast food around the area.

    \r\n
    \r\n
    \r\n Niagara Falls, ON, Canada \r\n 12:00 - 1:45 pm \r\n
    \r\n
    • \r\n
  • \r\n 5.\r\n

    Scenic drive on Niagara Parkway

    \r\n
    \r\n

    Travel along the famous Niagara Parkway along the Niagara River and admire the wonderful view.

    \r\n
    \r\n
    \r\n Niagara Parkway, Niagara Falls, ON, Canada \r\n 2:00 pm \r\n
    \r\n
    • \r\n
  • \r\n 6.\r\n

    Whirlpool Rapids

    \r\n
    \r\n

    Experience the natural phenomenon of the Niagara River. You will witness the power of the Niagara River and watch the white waters of the rapids in the Niagara Gorge. The waters of the rapids converge, causing them to spin in counterclockwise motion. At this time we drop off customers to the Helipad (if they have selected the Helicopter Tour Add-On).

    \r\n
    \r\n
    \r\n Niagara Falls, ON, Canada \r\n 2:15 pm \r\n
    \r\n
    • \r\n
  • \r\n 7.\r\n

    The Floral Clock

    \r\n
    \r\n

    The Floral Clock is one of Niagara Falls most popular attractions. It is a large clock surrounded by thousands of colourful flowers in the summer and fall months.

    \r\n
    \r\n
    \r\n Queenston Heights Park, Niagara Parkway, Niagara-on-the-Lake, ON, Canada \r\n 2:45 pm \r\n
    \r\n
    • \r\n
  • \r\n 8.\r\n

    Visit the World's Smallest Chapel

    \r\n
    \r\n

    We will stop at the Worlds Smallest Chapel, a wonderful place to take unique pictures at the miniature place of worship.

    \r\n
    \r\n
    \r\n Queenston Heights Park, Niagara Parkway, Niagara-on-the-Lake, ON, Canada \r\n 3:15 pm \r\n
    \r\n
    • \r\n
  • \r\n 9.\r\n

    Niagara-on-the-Lake Drive Through & Wine Tasting

    \r\n
    \r\n

    We will cruise through the quaint town of Niagara-on-the-Lake to see the wonderful 19th century Victorian architecture and then stop at a local winery to taste some of the finest wines Canada has to offer (grape juice tastings are also available).

    \r\n
    \r\n
    \r\n Niagara-on-the-Lake, ON, Canada \r\n 3:45 pm \r\n
    \r\n
    • \r\n
  • \r\n 10.\r\n

    Dropoff

    \r\n
    \r\n

    You are dropped off at your place of pickup after your Niagara Falls Day Tour Adventure! (dropoff time depends on local traffic conditions or delays)

    \r\n
    \r\n
    \r\n Toronto, ON, Canada \r\n 6:15- 7.15 pm \r\n
    \r\n
    • \r\n
